                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#87va">Fol. 87va</locus>: Scribe's note on completing the writing.  <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 87va: ዓዲ፡ ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ በዳኅና፡ ወበሰላም፡ ዘንተ፡ ስንክሳር፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ጉባዔ፡ ኵሉ፡ ጥበብ፡… ወዘኵሉ፡ መዋዕል፡ ሊተ፡ ለገብሩ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ኃይለ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ዘሰመዩኒ፡ ርእሰ፡ ደብር፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in hand a; it mentions the priest Ḫaylä ʾIyäsus as the one who completed the writing.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#184rc">Fol. 184rc</locus>: Scribe's note on completing the writing. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 184rc: ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ በዳኅና፡ ወበሰላም፡ ዘንተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ስንክሳር፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in hand b.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- On the incipit page (fol. 1), a chain of black and red dot asterisks is placed in the upper margin. &#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: fol. 31va.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of a cross (+), indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: fols. 4vb, 19ra, 33rb, 40vb, 46va.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines (┴), indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: fols. 49vc, 50ra, 53ra, 65vc.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines (├), indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: fol. 120ra.&#xD;
- Many omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 3rb, 3va, 4rc, 4va, 5vb, 6vb, 8ra, 9ra, 26rc, 48vb, 51va, 61vb.&#xD;
- Omitted words added at the beginning of the line: fols. 16va, 49ra, 58ra, 66va, 69va, 70va, 86ra.&#xD;
- Omitted words added at the end of the line: fols. 66vc, 71vc, 72vc.&#xD;
- Many corrections written over erasures: e.g., fols. 2va, 13rc, 16vc, 22rc, 27va, 34vc, 78vc.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with thin black lines:  fols. 6va, 13ra, 33vc, 70vb, 86ra, 86vb, 119ra, 156vb.&#xD;
- Many immediate corrections indicated by thin series of dashes above and below the word(s): e.g., fols. 12vc, 25ra, 42va, 55ra, 71vc, 82va, 132vc, 151vb, 170vc, 179ra.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubrication left unfilled: fols. 57rb, 91va, 116ra.&#xD;
- Damaged letters or words rewritten in a secondary hand in blue pen: fols. 11vc, 12ra, 39vc, 179vc, 180ra, 180vc.&#xD;
- The scribe left 14 lines empty: fol. 150vc.&#xD;
- The scribe left 2 lines empty: fol. 155vc.&#xD;
- Two lines written in a secondary hand in blue pen: 121va.&#xD;
- A commemorative notice on 5 Miyazya is written in the upper margin of the page on fol. 35r.&#xD;
- Names written in a secondary hand in brown ink over an erased name: Wälättä Täklä Haymanot (fol. 13ra), ʾabunä Wäldä Maryam (fol. 54rb), Gäbrä Täklä Haymanot (fols. 70vb and 86va), Gäbrä Mikaʾel (fol. 73vc), Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (fol. 78rb),Wälättä Mikaʾel (fol. 81vc).&#xD;
- Erased names: fols. 45vb, 95rc, 129ra, 139rb.&#xD;
- Scribbles: fols. 173r.&#xD;
- Illegible notes in pencil on fols. 1v and 184v.</item>
